verbose_text: When analysed by system organ class, the incidence of ' skin and subcutaneous tissue disorders ' was significantly higher in TN (9.39%, 20/213) than in TE (1.22%, 5/411) (p < 0.0001), which was mainly driven by the larger number of cases developing rash in TN (13 cases) than in TE (one case).
